<Description>
    <Header>
        <h5><b>DataSource Update</b></h5>
    </Header>
    <Content>
        <p>This sample demonstrates replacing the entire data source of a Line Chart at regular intervals, rather than incrementally updating individual points.</p>
        <p>Full datasource replacement is useful in scenarios such as periodic refreshes, batch-processed results, or recalculated analytics. In Blazor, updating the bound data collection automatically triggers a chart refresh without requiring manual redraw logic. The transition can be animated by enabling the <code>Enable</code> property in <code>ChartSeriesAnimation</code>.</p>
    </Content>
</Description>

